<TITLE> B.League award night deferred </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 23 (bdnews24.com)  The B. League Award Night has been deferred by four days and will now be held on July 29 (Wednesday) at the National Sports Council Tower auditorium. The award night of the second edition professional football league was originally scheduled for Saturday, but the Bangladesh Football Federation was forced to defer it due to non-availability of finance minister Abul Maal Abdul Muhith. Now, the state minister for youth and sports, Ahad Ali Sarker, will attend the function as the chief guest and hand over the trophies to B. League champions Dhaka Abahani and runners-up Mohammedan Sporting Club. Besides, the champions and runners-up will also receive a cheque for Tk 10 lakh and Tk 5 respectively. Third-placed Sheikh Russell and fourth-placed Brothers Union will get Tk 3 lakh and Tk 2 lakh. Awards for the best player, highest scorer of the league will also be presented. The BFF has also decided to award silverware to the champions and the runners-ups of the first, second and third division leagues also on the same date, said BFF general secretary Al Musabbir Sadi. A musical show performed by Mila will follow the presentation ceremon
